com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetBvtRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetBvtRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RecordKeyProvider, SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serializable

    public class GetBvtRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
implements RecordKeyProvider

    Retrieves the best version of truth (BVT) from the specified base object or package using a known key. The specified base object, or the parent of the specified package, must be a link style BO instead of a merge style BO. This option can be configured in the schema manager of the Hub Console. The BVT is calculated on the set of records belonging to the same link group as the input record key.

    Required Parameters:

    • SiperianObjectUid - Specifies the type and the name of the base object or package to be used by the API.
    • RecordKey - Specifies the key of the record that needs to be retrieved.
    Optional Parameters:

    • Effective Date - the date used to retrieve an effective period or remote package to be queried.
    • History Date - The history date for wich the request is executed

    You can include pending records in the BVT calculation if state management is enabled on the base object, or parent base object of the package, by adding setIncludePending(boolean) to the request.

    Usage Example:

    The following example gets the BVT for a record with ROWID_OBJECT key 21 from the package ADDRESS_UPDATE_PKG:

    //Construct the request
    GetBvtRequest getBvtRequest = new GetBvtRequest();
    getBvtRequest.setSiperianObjectUid(
       SiperianObjectType.PACKAGE.makeUid("ADDRESS_UPDATE") );
    RecordKey recordKey = new RecordKey();
    recordKey.setRowid( "21" );
    getBvtRequest.setRecordKey( recordKey );
    getBvtRequest.setIncludePending(false);
    GetBvtResponse getBvtResponse = (GetBvtResponse)
       sipClient.process ( getBvtRequest );

    See Also:
    GetBvtResponse, GetRequest, LinkRequest, UnlinkRequest, SiperianClient.process(SiperianRequest), Serialized Form

    API Pair: GetBvtResponse

    API Group: Data Retrieval
